<body>
    <nav class="navbar">
        <ul>
            <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="/admin">Admin Login</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <section class="content">
        <h1>Enter OTP</h1>
        <p>An OTP has been generated for your account. Please enter it below to verify your identity.</p>


        <p><strong>To retrieve your OTP, send a POST request to the <code>/reset/api/get-otp</code> endpoint
                with the following payload:</strong></p>
        <pre>
        {
            "username": "[username]",
            "password": "[password]" 
        }
        </pre>

        <p><strong>Example using <code>curl</code>:</strong></p>
        <pre>
        curl -X POST [BASE_URL]/reset/api/get-otp \
            -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
            -d '{
                "username": "[your_username]",
                "password": "[your_password]"
            }'
        </pre>

        <br><small> Just roll with it and pretend it's sending an OTP code to your phone or something, I'm too lazy to
            stand
            up
            an
            OTP server for a CTF challenge </small><br>

        <form method="POST" action="/reset/verify">
            <input type="hidden" name="username" value="<%= username %>" />
            <label for="otp">OTP:</label>
            <input type="text" name="otp" required />
            <button type="submit">Verify OTP</button>
        </form>
    </section>

